interpretations of a looming disaster. Yet the destination is far from predictable, as the book seeks to move beyond the words and genres through which destruction is often known. Instead, this journey into the morass of eradication offers a series of unexpected discoveries about what it means to inherit the troubled legacies of the past and how we can take responsibility for a more inclusive, sustainable future.An urgent and unsettling meditation on environmental change, Running Out is a revelatory account of family, complicity, loss, and what it means to find your way back home.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aGround waterzHigh Plains (U.S.). 0aGroundwaterzHigh Plains (U.S.). 0aWater supplyxSocial aspectszHigh Plains (U.S.). 0aWater-supplyxSocial aspectszHigh Plains (U.S.). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  aGreat Plains.  aHeartland.  aJulene Bair.  aOgallala Blue.  aSarah Smarsh.  aThe Ogallala Road.  aWilliam Ashworth.  abelonging.  aconservative America.  aconservative values.  aenvironment.  aenvironmental crisis.  aethnography.  aexclusion.  afamily histories.  afarm families.  aglobal warming.  agroundwater depletion.  amemoir.  amemory.  apartisanship.  apolarization.  aresource depletion.  arural life.  asustainability.  athe best memoirs.  awater crisis.  awater wars.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPr